body:
In commit "[util] add RunCommandParseJSON" (31cf68a3ad1f0a5537c8419e2912b55fbfb88fa0)

I think it would be better not to require output to be formatted on a single line. Also better to trigger an error if these is unexpected data after the first line:

```diff
--- a/src/util/system.cpp
+++ b/src/util/system.cpp
@@ -1188,10 +1188,8 @@ UniValue RunCommandParseJSON(const std::string& str_command, const std::string&
     }
     stdin_stream.pipe().close();
 
-    std::string result;
-    std::string error;
-    std::getline(stdout_stream, result);
-    std::getline(stderr_stream, error);
+    std::string result{std::istreambuf_iterator<char>(stdout_stream), {}};
+    std::string error{std::istreambuf_iterator<char>(stderr_stream), {}};
 
     c.wait();
     const int n_error = c.exit_code();
```
